item.title: Connections
item.dc:creator: @Unhandled Unhandled
item.description:
@Unhandled wrote:

[quote=“zstars, post:11, topic:198434”][quote author=zyle1992 link=topic=263099.msg2178635#msg2178635 date=1207907981]
and then keep making new deobs every time they update something, tossing out the work i did on the previous deob, and find out what everything does on the new deob? non gracias et non bueno
[/quote]

If you don’t want to do that, don’t worry. You just have to locate every packet building code so that you can change every single packet opcode to its new homologue. After that you simply have to check every packet building code so that you make sure that the endianness and coding of every variable in the packet matches.
After that you have to fix any inconsistencies which will probably arise from the version mismatch, including but not limited to bot-detection traps, to cache problems, and to new or completely modified outgoing and / or incoming packets.

After doing all this, you still have work, but I suggest that you do it all again. Because by the time you’re done, RS will have been updated again. (Or Runescape and all who knew it will be long dead and forgotten).[/quote]
Or just use a bytecode library and write an updater to modify the client with, rather that deobfuscating it and getting banned?

Read full topic
